<CaseStudyLayout
  title="Greenroom"
  subtitle="A personal log for live music lovers to document and revisit concerts."
  category="Mobile App"
  year="2024"
  description="Greenroom — a concert logging app by Mackenzie Hart"
  role="Product Designer"
  duration="8 weeks"
>
  <section>
    <h2>Overview</h2>
    <p>
      Greenroom is for people who live for live music. Setlists, moments, the
      feeling of a particular venue on a particular night — all of it tends to
      blur over time. The app gives concertgoers a quiet, personal place to
      capture and revisit shows, without the performative pressure of social
      sharing.
    </p>
    <p>
      The design leans into the textures of the experience itself: ticket stubs,
      backstage passes, handwritten notes.
    </p>
  </section>

  <div class="callout">
    <p>"How might we help music fans hold onto the feeling of a show, not just the facts?"</p>
  </div>

